 Topics Learned – Cyber Security Learning Path

 Cybersecurity Foundations
- Understanding cybersecurity roles (Red Team vs Blue Team)  
- CIA Triad (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)  
- Threats, vulnerabilities, and risk management  
- Overview of real-world cyber attacks  

Networking & Communication
- TCP/IP and OSI models  
- Common protocols (HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, FTP, SSH)  
- Network services and how they are exploited  
- Network reconnaissance techniques  

 Linux Fundamentals
- Linux file system and directory structure  
- Command-line operations and navigation  
- File permissions and user management  
- Process and service handling  

 Reconnaissance & Enumeration
- Passive reconnaissance (whois, DNS lookup)  
- Active reconnaissance (ping, traceroute)  
- Port scanning and service detection using Nmap  
